## Context

`workflow.md` originally announced the current Dragon Dreaming phase at session
start (`[→ Imagine]`, `[→ Plan]`, `[→ Execute]`, `[→ Verify]`). This was removed
in commit `be15b29` ("fix: resolve bugs and stale references") as collateral damage
when the worktree hook plumbing changed. The phase column was dropped from the
context→worktree table without deliberate intent.

The feature was lightweight: one label emitted after `EnterWorktree`, inferred from
conversation context (fresh explore → Imagine, ticket ref → Plan, active branch →
Execute, PR review → Verify). It gave the user an orientation signal at session open.

## Question

Is the phase signal worth restoring? It costs one line of model output per session.
Benefit: user immediately sees which claw they're in. Risk: model may mis-infer the
phase, creating noise rather than signal.

Alternative: emit it only on explicit `/perch`, not automatically at session start.
